Plus, this little-known iPhone feature safeguarded a reporters data from feds and it could save yours, too

Too Many Toots? What Excessive Farting Says About Your Health.
 
 
Whether it happens on your postprandial fart walk, right in the middle of yoga class or while youre sleeping, everyone even the poshest among us farts. Doctors share their thoughts on whats normal when it comes to gas and what needs to be checked out.

Leadership contact update Re: Cleaning Matthew
html_body:
Thank you for your note.  Starting January 1, 2026 I will be focused on my Board Director role at Splendid Spoon Inc and stepping back from Mosaic and Splendid Spoon day-to-day.  I will not be monitoring this inbox, so please direct business matters as follows:

Business Partnerships - Nicole Centeno, co-CEO (nicole@splendidspoon.com)
Finance & Legal - Elise Densborn, co-CEO (elise@splendidspoon.com)
Operations - Jose Sanchez, VP of Operations (jose.sanchez@mosaicfoods.com)

For personal or board-related matters, please do reach out to me directly via email or text.  Happy New Year!

Best,
Matt


--


Matt Davis
Co-founder

subject: Thank you for your email Re: Cleaners
html_body:
THIS EMAIL IS NOT MONITORED 24/7.

Note to patients: Communication via email is for logistical and administrative purposes only. Clinical content should not be sent via email. Any information other than administrative will be addressed by your clinician at your next scheduled appointment. If this is a psychiatric emergency and you can not wait for help or feel unsafe, please call 911 immediately or go to your nearest Emergency Room.


Friendly Reminder: To ensure fairness to both our clients and staff, we kindly ask for at least 24 hours' notice to cancel or reschedule appointments. For sessions scheduled weekends or holidays, 48 hours' notice is appreciated. Appointments canceled late, or missed entirely, may be subject to a $150 fee. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation.

In case of emergency: Please be aware that the use of email is a form of communication for convenience and that emails cannot be used for communicating emergency or life-threatening situations. 
  • If you are experiencing an emergency or life-threatening situation, call 911 or go to your nearest emergency room. 
  • The National Suicide Prevention Hotline can be reached by calling or texting 988. 

Disclaimer: E-mail is not necessarily a confidential or secure method of communication. The content or materials in this e-mail are private and may contain Protected Health Information. Your use of e-mail constitutes your acknowledgment of these confidentiality and security limitations. Email is to be used for logistical purposes only, all clinical communications must take place in session.

If you are not the intended recipient, be advised that any unauthorized use, disclosure, copying, distribution, or the taking of any action in reliance on the contents of this information is strictly prohibited. If you have received this e-mail in error, please immediately notify the sender via telephone or return e-mail, then please destroy this communication.

html_body:
THIS EMAIL IS NOT MONITORED 24/7.

Note to patients: Communication via email is for logistical and administrative purposes only. Clinical content should not be sent via email. Any information other than administrative will be addressed by your clinician at your next scheduled appointment. If this is a psychiatric emergency and you can not wait for help or feel unsafe, please call 911 immediately or go to your nearest Emergency Room.


Friendly Reminder: To ensure fairness to both our clients and staff, we kindly ask for at least 24 hours' notice to cancel or reschedule appointments. For sessions scheduled weekends or holidays, 48 hours' notice is appreciated. Appointments canceled late, or missed entirely, may be subject to a $150 fee. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation.

In case of emergency: Please be aware that the use of email is a form of communication for convenience and that emails cannot be used for communicating emergency or life-threatening situations. 
  • If you are experiencing an emergency or life-threatening situation, call 911 or go to your nearest emergency room. 
  • The National Suicide Prevention Hotline can be reached by calling or texting 988. 

Disclaimer: E-mail is not necessarily a confidential or secure method of communication. The content or materials in this e-mail are private and may contain Protected Health Information. Your use of e-mail constitutes your acknowledgment of these confidentiality and security limitations. Email is to be used for logistical purposes only, all clinical communications must take place in session.

If you are not the intended recipient, be advised that any unauthorized use, disclosure, copying, distribution, or the taking of any action in reliance on the contents of this information is strictly prohibited. If you have received this e-mail in error, please immediately notify the sender via telephone or return e-mail, then please destroy this communication.

subject: Auto response: Please Read - Tis the Season for Good Communication Re: Cleaning quote
html_body:
January 2026 UPDATES: There is an upcoming switch to Fullscript for cash pay and specialty labs in 2026 instead of Rupa health.

Fullscript lets you order labs and supplements in one secure place, gives you transparent cash-pay procing and allows you to pay the lab directly without involving insurance.
Short patient script (verbal or handout)

Fullscript offers better integration of labs and supplements, clearer pricing, and a smoother checkout process. It also gives you direct access to your orders and results in one portal.

Is this covered by insurance?

These are specialty functional labs, which are usually not covered by insurance anyway. Using a cash-pay platform like Fullscript avoids surprise bills and lets you see the exact price upfront. 

Fall 2025 UPDATES (PLEASE READ):As of October 8, 2025, Dr. Yvonne will no longer be in network for Providence. Patients can instead pay at the time of service and we will provide you with a superbill to submit to your insurance for reimbursement or we can help you find another provider who is in your network. Please reach out to your insurance company directly if any questions about your individual plan related to these changes. 

VA UPDATE: Holly has now permanently taken over for Katy. Please be sure to reach out to her via email with any questions or booking inquiries. 


A friendly reminder if needing refills please have your Pharmacy fax a Refill Request to (503) 293-2023.


Please reserve Direct Messaging in Jane to Dr. Yvonne for urgent medical related inquiries.


Due to the recent high volume of patient care, if you have any questions or acute matters, please schedule a Momentum Visit or a Strategy Visit with Dr. Yvonne online.


Dr. Yvonne's new patient facing hours will be Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays 12:00 pm - 5:00 pm for both in-person and telemedicine. 


Please note: Please note that lab orders may take longer than usual as we are currently transitioning back to paper. When you receive a document from Dr. Yvonne, please be sure to open it, as it may contain your lab order.


Please note that to manage our high workload, we request one email per week per sender (regarding questions, updates, documents, etc). Thank you for your understanding.


**NOTE:  If you are having a medical emergency please call 911 or visit your nearest Emergency Department or Urgent Care, do not leave us an email here.** 

2025 Workflow:

1.  **Lab orders-** LabCorp and Quest are electronic, others get posted to your Janeapp account within a week of your visit.  If in a week you don't see them, please email Siobhan at frontdesk@dryvonne.com. 

**If you haven't had a visit in 4-6 months, we require a **momentum lab order visit to make sure all will be covered by the order. **

2. **Refills** - Always check your bottle first.  If out, please request from your pharmacy directly and have them fax us at **503-293-2023**. These may take up to 7 business days to process completely, so please do not wait until the last minute. 

NOTE: many pharmacies will grant you a temporary refill to last until the 90 day gets processed, just ask!
If you do not get your refills within the week, please let us know by phone or hello@dryvonne.com.

3.  **Lab results**- once received, they will get posted to your Janeapp account (not email) and you will be notified to book via email.  If you get results and don't hear from us, we may have not received them at the clinic yet, pls email them to hello@dryvonne.com and let us know, thx!

4.  **Communication flow**- phone messages get checked twice daily on East Coast Time. You should hear back from Holly within the next business day, if not, please call us back.  Phone calls are returned first.  Emails to hello@dryvonne.com are checked 2nd and may take 24-48 hrs to return if Holly needs to talk to me, since she is virtual.

5.  **Cancellations**-we request 48 hrs, to be able to open the spot for another patient who needs it.  There will be a fee if not cancelled in the 48hr window, unless under special circumstances. Thank you for your understanding.

6.  **Visit summaries**- will get posted to Fullscript within a week of your visit, if you haven't received the update in the body of the text, please reach out to frontdesk@dryvonne.com.

7.  **Updated Insurance 2025**-if new insurance for 2025, pls take a picture of the front and back of your card and email to frontdesk@dryvonne.com before your first visit of the year. I am currently contracted with Regence and Moda only. Others are out of network and we request payment at the time of your visit and we will issue you a Superbill to submit to insurance for reimbursement if you have an out of network benefit.  Best for you to call and double check before trying though!

           **Dr Yvonne's Winter 2025 OFFICE HOURS: Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday Noon-5pm, earlier by  special arrangement.**  NOTE: If Inclement weather, we will switch you to a virtual visit, if no power, we will reach out via phone with updates.

                                                      **IMPORTANT 2025 Insurance Updates**
Currently I am contracted with Regence Blue Cross Blue Shield of Oregon, and Moda Health.  All others will be out of network and we will provide you a receipt to submit  to your insurance for possible reimbursement.


--




Holly Faulkner (she/her)

Assistant to Dr. Yvonne Kreger

For online booking click here
text_body:

Fullscript lets you order labs and supplements in one secure place, gives you transparent cash-pay procing and allows you to pay the lab directly without involving insurance.
Short patient script (verbal or handout)

Fullscript offers better integration of labs and supplements, clearer pricing, and a smoother checkout process. It also gives you direct access to your orders and results in one portal.

Is this covered by insurance?

These are specialty functional labs, which are usually not covered by insurance anyway. Using a cash-pay platform like Fullscript avoids surprise bills and lets you see the exact price upfront.

html_body:
Hello and thank you for contacting Gail Yazzolino.

The staff and community of Historic Oregon City, Clackamas Heritage Partners are happy to announce that Gail has begun her next great adventure, retirement. We miss her greatly and are deeply thankful for her 20 years of service to the organization. 

This email is no longer forwarded and We encourage you to contact our new Executive Director, Corinne Lowenthal at Corinne@historicoregoncity.org

We look forward to continuing to serve you.


--

Best regards,
Gail Yazzolino

Historic Oregon City, Clackamas Heritage Partners
End of the Oregon Trail Interpretive & Visitor Information Center
1726 Washington Street, Oregon City, OR 97045
503-657-9336 ext. 107   Fax 503-557-8590
www.historicoregoncity.org

subject: Rescind Boil Water Notification - City of Harker Heights
html_body:
Rescind Boil Water Notification - City of Harker Heights - PWS 0140023

The February 2, 2026, Boil Water Order has been lifted for the following areas:

1900 Wolverine Trail through 1906 Wolverine Trail
505 Lobo Trail through 519 Lobo Trail
512 Dingo Circle through 519 Dingo Circle
602 Dingo through 605 Dingo

Normal water usage may resume immediately. Service has been restored, and all water quality tests have been completed. The water is now safe to drink and use without boiling.

TCEQ Required Notice

On February 2, 2026 the Texas Commission on Environmental Quality required the City of Harker Heights public water system, PWS ID #0140023, to issue a Boil Water Notice to inform customers, individuals, or employees that due to conditions which occurred recently in the public water system, the water from this public water system was required to be boiled prior to use for drinking water or human consumption purposes.

The public water system has taken the necessary corrective actions to restore the quality of the water distributed by this public water system used for drinking water or human consumption purposes and has provided TCEQ with laboratory test results that indicate that the water no longer requires boiling prior to use as of February 5, 2026.

If you have questions regarding this matter, you can contact:
Public Works Department at 254-953-5649,
John McElroy, Public Works Director at 254-953-5613
Mark Hyde, Assistant City Manager at 254-953-5641 or
David Mitchell, City Manager at 254-953-5600

  • bwn 2.jpg

Update your subscriptions, modify your password or email address, or stop subscriptions at any time on your Subscriber Preferences Page. You will need to use your email address to log in. If you have questions or problems with the subscription service, please visit subscriberhelp.govdelivery.com.

This service is provided to you at no charge by Harker Heights, TX.

Thank you for contacting mycareer@travelandleisure.com for a Reasonable Accommodation Request.

This specific mailbox is to support Travel + Leisure Co. applicants who require reasonable accommodation/s to complete their application or any part of the recruiting process. If your email is requesting a reasonable accommodation, an HR Representative will be in touch soon.

All other inquiries, please see below.

Completed Application:
If you are inquiring about a position for which you recently applied, a recruiter will review your qualifications/background and contact you directly if you have been selected to move forward in the process.

Interested In Position/s:
If you are interested in working for Travel + Leisure Co., please visit our careers website at www.travelandleisurecareers.com to view and apply for positions that match your interests and experience. Upon completion of your online application, which may include an assessment, a recruiter will contact you directly if you have been selected to move forward to next steps.

Technical Issues:
If your email is related to an online application technical issue, it will be forwarded to our HRIS team for support/resolution.

All other emails unrelated to accommodation requests will not be addressed through this mail box.

All the best,

Travel and Leisure Careers

subject: Hello from Chip @ Southwest Cloud Partners
html_body:
Darcy, 

I noticed your website (xcleanlv.com) is in Lovable, how is that working out for you?

I wanted to introduce myself, my name is Chip and I am CEO of Southwest Cloud Partners, a full stack IT services provider in Las Vegas.

Do you manage your own IT needs?

Do you use a CRM to track client appointments and which service agents to send? 

What are you using for email outreach?

My target market is small businesses so I'm really curious what other tools you are using that are working for you.  Amazing website by the way!

subject: Hey, feeling lucky?
html_body:
OPEN UP IF YOU LIKE FREE THINGS
;1mportant Privacy Information - Especially for Plain Text Readers Hi [Recipient Name], This message is particularly important for those of you reading this in plain text, which often means you're using an older device. We know that users like you are often more interested in privacy policies and how companies manage their data. Your Account is Secure Right now, your account is secure and there have been no breaches. We're committed to being proactive about your privacy, taking preventative measures to safeguard your data. Why We're Contacting You We believe in transparency and want to ensure you have all the information you need to stay safe online. While we employ the latest security measures to protect your account, it's equally important for you to be informed and vigilant, especially if you're using an older device. What to Do if You Suspect an Issue In the unlikely event of a security issue, we want you to be prepared. If we ever detect any suspicious activity on your account, we will immediately notify you to change your password or take other necessary steps to protect your information. Here are some potential triggers for security alerts: Suspicious login attempts from an unrecognized device or location. Changes to your account settings that you did not authorize. Potential unauthorized access to your personal information. Proactive Security Measures We take a proactive approach to security, constantly monitoring our systems and implementing the latest security protocols to protect your data. This includes: Robust encryption to safeguard your personal and financial information. Strict access controls to limit access to your data. Regular security audits to identify and address potential vulnerabilities. Comprehensive incident response plans to handle any security incidents swiftly and effectively. Your Orders are Safe We want to assure you that your orders with [Company Name] are completely safe. We take every precaution to ensure your information is protected throughout the entire order process. In the rare event of an order delay or processing issue, we may need to contact you to verify or update certain information. This may include: Confirming your shipping address Clarifying order details Providing updates on the estimated delivery time Important Security Reminder Please remember that we will never ask you for sensitive information such as your credit card number, expiry date, or CVV via email. Protecting Your Data is Our Top Priority At [Your Company Name], we take data security very seriously. We have implemented robust measures to protect your information, including: Multi-Factor Authentication: Add an extra layer of security by enabling multi-factor authentication on your account. Strong Password Policies: Use a strong, unique password for your account and change it regularly. Regular Security Audits: We conduct regular security audits to identify and address potential vulnerabilities. Incident Response Plans: We have well-defined incident response plans to handle any data breach or security incident. Even though you are safe, this is important - in this event we may also ask you to: Take Action Now: Click on the following link to verify your account: [Insert Link Here] Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the verification process. As a heads up: We will also try to inform you of any suspicious activity on your account. Here's an example of what that might look like: Recent Activity Summary: Date: [Date of suspicious activity] Time: [Time of suspicious activity] Location: [Location of suspicious activity] Device: [Device used for suspicious activity] Action: [Description of suspicious activity, e.g., login attempt, password reset request, etc.] If you do not recognize this activity, please reply to this email with the subject line "Unauthorized Access" and we will take immediate steps to secure your account. We may also ask you to take the following Additional Security Measures: Change your password: Choose a strong, unique password that is at least 12 characters long and includes a combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols. Enable two-factor authentication: This adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second form of verification, such as a code sent to your phone, in addition to your password. Thank you for your attention to this important matter. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a safe and secure online experience. Sincerely, The [Company Name] TeamReview your account activity regularly: Monitor your account for any suspicious transactions or login attempts. Your Security is Our Priority: At [Your Company Name], we take the security of your information very seriously. We're committed to employing the latest security technologies and best practices to protect your data. If you have any questions or concerns about your account security, please don't hesitate to contact us. Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter. Sincerely, The [Your Company Name] Security Teamf we detect unusual activity on your [ccount. To ensure the security of your personal information, we will require you to DO NOT give us credit card information like your full 16 digit number to verify your identity immediately this may be a phising attempt and they can take your informationwithin 24 hours may result in temporary suspension of your access. Take Action Now if we ever have an issue
